parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected detachment of the T-Top can cause a loud noise, startled reaction, and potential loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The T-Top blows off or explodes while driving
often accompanied by a loud noise
and leaving only the rubber seal and locking bar remaining.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to unexpected loss of power while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine will not start
the car will shut off without notice while driving
difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel line leaks can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard, and can also lead to engine stalling or failure, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
high-pressure fuel return line leaks
fuel smell
engine stalling or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power windows can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and in some cases, may obstruct the driver's view.
symptoms: Power windows will not open or close
both driver and passenger side power windows are affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes all the way to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.
